measure_df <- lapply(paste0("measures_df_25_shared_w", c(1, 5, 10), ".csv"), function(fp){
  read.csv(fp) %>%
    mutate(
      window_size=as.integer(gsub("measures_df_25_shared_w|\\.csv", "", fp))
    ) %>%
    mutate(
      first_vec_dist=round(as.double(vec_corr_dist), 4),
      second_vec_global_dist=round(as.double(global_corr_dist), 4),
      second_vec_local_dist=round(as.double(local_corr_dist), 4)
    ) %>%
    rename(T2=dynasty) %>%
    select(char, T2, first_vec_dist, second_vec_global_dist, second_vec_local_dist, window_size)
}) %>%
  bind_rows()

measure_df_long <- measure_df %>%
  melt(id=c("window_size", "char", "T2"), variable.name="dist_measure", value.name="dist")

measure_df_long$T2 <- factor(measure_df_long$T2, levels=T2_lst)

draw_VNC <- function(data, distance_measure, facet_title, window_size, dist_measure){ # options: "cv", "sd"
  par(new=TRUE, cex.main=1.5, cex.lab=1.5, cex.axis=0.995)
  distance.measure <- distance_measure
  
  input <- data[, 3]
  years <- data[, 2]
  names(input) <- years
  xlabels <- years
  
  data.collector <- list()
  data.collector[["0"]] <- input
  position.collector <- list()
  position.collector[[1]] <- 0
  overall.distance <- 0
  number.of.steps <- length(input) - 1
  
  dist_lst <- c() #
  for (i in 1:number.of.steps) {
      cat(i/number.of.steps, "\n", sep = "")
      difference.checker <- numeric()
      for (j in 1:(length(unique(names(input))) - 1)) {
          first.name <- unique(names(input))[j]
          second.name <- unique(names(input))[(j + 1)]
          pooled.sample <- input[names(input) %in% c(first.name, 
              second.name)]
          if (distance.measure == "sd"){
        difference.checker[j] <- ifelse(sum(pooled.sample) == 
              0, 0, sd(pooled.sample))
    }
    else if (distance.measure == "cv"){
        difference.checker[j] <- ifelse(sum(pooled.sample) == 
              0, 0, sd(pooled.sample)/mean(pooled.sample))
    }
      }
  
  
      pos.to.be.merged <- which.min(difference.checker)
      distance <- min(difference.checker)
      dist_lst <- c(dist_lst, distance) #
      overall.distance <- overall.distance + distance
      lower.name <- unique(names(input))[pos.to.be.merged]
      higher.name <- unique(names(input))[(pos.to.be.merged + 
          1)]
      matches <- names(input) %in% c(lower.name, higher.name)
      new.mean.age <- round(mean(as.numeric(names(input)[names(input) %in% 
          c(lower.name, higher.name)])), 4)
      position.collector[[(i + 1)]] <- which(names(input) == 
          lower.name | names(input) == higher.name)
      names(input)[names(input) %in% c(lower.name, higher.name)] <- as.character(new.mean.age)
      data.collector[[(i + 1)]] <- input
      names(data.collector)[(i + 1)] <- distance
  }
  if (distance.measure == "sd"){
  plot(0, mean(years), xlim = range(years), ylim = c(0, 1.1 * 
    sum(as.numeric(names(data.collector)))), main = "", 
    xlab = "Year", ylab = "Distance in summed standard deviations", 
    type = "n", axes = FALSE)
    
  } else if (distance.measure == "cv"){
  plot(0, mean(years), xlim = range(years), ylim = c(0, 1.1 * 
    sum(as.numeric(names(data.collector)))), main = "", 
    xlab = "Year", ylab = "Distance in summed CVs", 
    type = "n", axes = FALSE)   
  }
  
  grid()
  axis(1, at = years, labels=xlabels)
  axis(2)
  #axis(4, at = input)
  
  cur.y <- rep(0, length(data.collector[[1]]))
  for (k in 1:(length(data.collector) - 1)) {
      cur.x <- as.numeric(unique(names(data.collector[[k]])))
      arrows(cur.x, cur.y, cur.x, cur.y + as.numeric(unique(names(data.collector[(k + 
          1)]))), length = 0)
      cur.y <- rep(unique(cur.y) + as.numeric(unique(names(data.collector[(k + 
          1)]))), length(cur.x) - 1)
      left <- min(position.collector[[(k + 1)]])
      right <- max(position.collector[[(k + 1)]])
      lower.x <- as.numeric(names(data.collector[[k]])[left])
      higher.x <- as.numeric(names(data.collector[[k]])[right])
      arrows(lower.x, unique(cur.y), higher.x, unique(cur.y), 
          length = 0)
  }
  par(new=TRUE)
  plot(years, input, type="l", col = "blue",              # Create second plot without axes
       axes = FALSE, xlab = "", ylab = "")
  
  axis(side = 4, at = pretty(range(input)))      # Add second axis
  
  #title(main=facet_title)
  
  return(rev(dist_lst))
}
lapply(c("Window size = 1", "Window size = 5", "Window size = 10"), function(ws){
  lapply(c("First embeddings", "Second embeddings\n(Global measure)", "Second embeddings\n(Local measure)"), function(dm){
    # data prep
    freq_lst <- measure_df_long %>%
      filter(
        char=="",
        window_size==ws,
        dist_measure==dm
      ) %>%
      pull(dist)
    df <- data.frame(
      ID=1:5,
      YEAR=c(960, 1271, 1368, 1644, 1980),
      FREQUENCY=freq_lst
    )
    
    # draw VNC
    dev.new()
    
    if(dm=="First embeddings"){
      dm_fn <- "first_embed"
    }else if(dm=="Second embeddings\n(Global measure)"){
      dm_fn <- "second_embed_global"
    }else if(dm=="Second embeddings\n(Local measure)"){
      dm_fn <- "second_embed_local"
    }
    
    ws_fn <- gsub("Window size = ", "", ws)
    
    pdf(paste0("VNC_measure_dist_w", ws_fn,"_", dm_fn, ".pdf"), width=10, height=10)
    scree_dist_lst <- draw_VNC(df, distance_measure="cv", facet_title=paste0(ws, "\n", dm),
                               window_size=ws, dist_measure=dm)
    dev.off()
    
    scree_df <- data.frame(
      window_size=ws,
      dist_measure=dm,
      cluster_num=1:4,
      scree_dist=scree_dist_lst
    )
    return(scree_df)
  }) %>%
    bind_rows()
}) %>%
  bind_rows() -> scree_dist_df
